endogenously reproduce complex dynamics, from small fluctuations to
large crises, due to innovation and industrial dynamics, rising
inequality and financial instability, and so on. The integration between
AB macroeconomics and the (post-Keynesian) stock-flow consistent
approach represents a promising way for the future development of this
research field.},
